{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd3913a1-ba9f-49d3-9eac-c272ec2da904","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended pattern is **constructor injection** for `TestContext` combined with `[ClassInitialize]`/`[TestInitialize]` for async setup:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init here (e.g., setting up simple objects)\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test initialization (e.g., DB connections, HTTP clients)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task ClassSetup(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // One-time async setup for the class (shared expensive resources)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(TestContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — synchronous init; receives `TestContext` via DI (MSTest v3+)\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — supports `async Task`; runs before each test for async setup\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — one-time async setup shared across all tests in the class\n\nThe constructor runs before `[TestInitialize]`, so put cheap/sync work in the constructor and async/expensive work in `[TestInitialize]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5efa29b7-63f8-4954-b70e-ffa947a5d7b9","outputTokens":402,"requestId":"BD05:1A8D4E:1E2897A:2214F00:6A07CBB5"},"id":"04e71038-f278-4e38-901c-0d0d06215c0b","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:43:26.534Z","parentId":"2f4822dc-2bef-4b30-8b95-2bea62209033"}
